      <bioghist id="aspace_9fd78e7cc06119dfadc7670dba3c1674">
         <head>COUNTEE CULLEN (1903-1946)</head>
         <p>Recognized at an early age for his poetic gift, Cullen became one of the leading lights of the Harlem Renaissance. Following the success of his volumes of poems, he studied in France on a Guggenheim Fellowship, married Yolande DuBois, the daughter of W.E.B. DuBois, and taught in the New York City school system.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_568de54b530aecad08bd3ad398d430b3">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection contains materials relating to Countee Cullen.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
